Samsung has launched its new Galaxy A6+ smartphone in South Africa, sporting a stylish design and powerful specifications. The Galaxy A6+ boasts the manufacturer’s Infinity display design and comes in Gold, Black, and Lavender finishes. Samsung’s Galaxy A6+ also features an impressive camera system, with a 24MP front-facing sensor and a dual camera setup on the rear of the smartphone. The device supports the AI-powered Bixby Vision camera feature, which recognises objects, landmarks, and more. Samsung’s Bixby digital assistant is also included in the device, along with AI-powered features such as Bixby Home and Reminder. South African customers who purchase the Galaxy A6+ will also receive a complimentary 64GB memory card. The device will be available in local stores from 1 June 2018 and is priced at R6,499.  